theorem interior_inter_left_isOpen {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A B : Set X}
    (hA : IsOpen (A : Set X)) :
    interior (A ∩ B : Set X) = A ∩ interior (B : Set X) := by
  apply Set.Subset.antisymm
  · -- `interior (A ∩ B) ⊆ A ∩ interior B`
    intro x hx
    have hAB : (x : X) ∈ (A ∩ B : Set X) := interior_subset hx
    have hIntB : (x : X) ∈ interior (B : Set X) :=
      (interior_mono (Set.inter_subset_right : (A ∩ B : Set X) ⊆ B)) hx
    exact And.intro hAB.1 hIntB
  · -- `A ∩ interior B ⊆ interior (A ∩ B)`
    intro x hx
    rcases hx with ⟨hxA, hxIntB⟩
    -- Use the open set `A ∩ interior B` contained in `A ∩ B`
    have hOpen : IsOpen ((A ∩ interior (B : Set X)) : Set X) :=
      hA.inter isOpen_interior
    have hSubset : (A ∩ interior (B : Set X) : Set X) ⊆ A ∩ B := by
      intro y hy
      exact ⟨hy.1, (interior_subset : interior (B : Set X) ⊆ B) hy.2⟩
    have hxIn : (x : X) ∈ (A ∩ interior (B : Set X)) := And.intro hxA hxIntB
    exact mem_interior.2 ⟨A ∩ interior (B : Set X), hOpen, hSubset, hxIn⟩

theorem openInterInterior_subset_and_open {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X]
    {A B : Set X} (hA : IsOpen (A : Set X)) :
    (A ∩ interior (B : Set X) : Set X) ⊆ A ∩ B ∧
      IsOpen (A ∩ interior (B : Set X)) := by
  refine And.intro ?_ ?_
  · -- Subset part
    intro x hx
    rcases hx with ⟨hAx, hIntBx⟩
    have hBx : (x : X) ∈ (B : Set X) :=
      interior_subset (s := B) hIntBx
    exact And.intro hAx hBx
  · -- Openness part
    exact hA.inter isOpen_interior
